I’ll keep this strictly read-only and verify against upstream sources, starting with the requested raw docs plus the repository tree/package metadata.
The requested `AGENTS.md` fetch returned 404; the repository tree confirms no root `AGENTS.md` is checked in. I’m using `CLAUDE.md`, `REFERENCE.md`, `package.json`, the repo tree, and selected source/docs to fill gaps and verify the command surface.
I found the daemon is not a Unix socket: source shows an HTTP server on `127.0.0.1` with a default port and token header, plus a WebSocket path for the safe-mode plugin bridge. Next I’m checking the command registration and generated-agent files from source.
To avoid missing source-only commands, I’m doing a read-only remote source scan of `src/commands/*.js` and selected files for Commander registrations and MCP references.
The remote scan found no `mcp` or “Model Context Protocol” references in README, REFERENCE, CLAUDE, package metadata, docs, source, or plugin files. That points to no bundled figma-cli MCP server; I’m checking design-system format details before writing the final synthesis.
## IT1 — figma-cli capabilities

### Install & prerequisites

| Item | Finding |
|---|---|
| Primary package name | Repo `package.json` names the package `figma-ds-cli`, version `1.2.0`, with binaries `figma-ds-cli` and `figma-cli` both resolving to `src/index.js`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/package.json |
| Public npm status | npm registry currently reports `figma-ds-cli@1.0.0`, whose `bin` only exposes `figma-ds-cli`, not `figma-cli`. This conflicts with repo `main` and the repo changelog claim that `npx figma-ds-cli` installs both binaries. Sources: https://registry.npmjs.org/figma-ds-cli/latest, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/CHANGELOG.md |
| Practical install path | Repo README pushes users to download/clone `github.com/silships/figma-cli`, run setup from the project, and let Claude/Cursor run `npm install` and connect. npm page says `npm install -g figma-ds-cli` and `npx figma-ds-cli`, but that appears older than repo `main`. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/README.md, https://www.npmjs.com/package/figma-ds-cli |
| PATH command | From repo `main`, `figma-cli` resolves to `src/index.js`; from current npm latest, only `figma-ds-cli` is guaranteed. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/package.json |
| Node version | `engines.node` is `>=18`; setup code also exits if Node major is below 18. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/package.json, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/setup.js |
| Figma prerequisite | Requires Figma Desktop, open with a Figma file. README says no API key and local Desktop control. npm page says Figma Desktop with a free account works. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/README.md, https://www.npmjs.com/package/figma-ds-cli |
| OS/platform | Architecture doc says “macOS only (for now)”; npm page says macOS, Windows/Linux coming. Source code contains platform helpers for macOS, Windows, and Linux paths/commands, but the docs still treat macOS as the supported path. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/platform.js |
| Requested fetch failures | `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/AGENTS.md` returned 404. Repo tree confirms no root `AGENTS.md`; `init-agent` generates one for consuming projects. Source tree: https://api.github.com/repos/silships/figma-cli/git/trees/main?recursive=1 |

### Connection modes (yolo vs safe) + daemon lifecycle

| Area | Finding |
|---|---|
| Yolo command | `figma-cli connect` uses Yolo Mode. It patches Figma Desktop, restarts Figma with remote debugging, waits for CDP, then starts the speed daemon. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/README.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/setup.js |
| Safe command | `figma-cli connect --safe` starts the daemon in plugin mode, does not patch Figma, and instructs the user to import `plugin/manifest.json` once, then open `Plugins → Development → FigCli` each session. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/REFERENCE.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/setup.js |
| Yolo patch mechanics | Patch reads Figma’s `app.asar`, replaces `removeSwitch("remote-debugging-port")` with `removeSwitch("remote-debugXing-port")`, and on macOS attempts `codesign --force --deep --sign - /Applications/Figma.app`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/figma-patch.js |
| Revert command | `figma-cli unpatch` restores the original string and updates local config; source description: “Restore Figma to original state (removes remote debugging patch).” Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/setup.js |
| CDP port | Yolo uses Chrome DevTools Protocol on fixed port `9222`; source says this is fixed for `figma-use` compatibility. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/figma-patch.js |
| Daemon transport | The daemon is an HTTP server on `127.0.0.1`, default port `3456`, not a Unix socket. It exposes `/health`, `/exec`, `/reconnect`, and WebSocket `/plugin` for safe-mode plugin connections. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/daemon.js |
| Daemon security | Requires `X-Daemon-Token`, validates host as `localhost` or `127.0.0.1`, blocks CORS preflight, and stores token at `~/.figma-ds-cli/.daemon-token`. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/daemon.js, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/lib/cli-core.js |
| Daemon PID/model | PID file is `~/.figma-cli-daemon.pid`; daemon is spawned detached via Node. It does not survive OS reboot as a process, but CLI can restart it if prior setup state exists. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/lib/cli-core.js |
| Idle lifecycle | Code default idle timeout is `60 * 60 * 1000` ms, i.e. 60 minutes. The header comment says 10 minutes, but executable code uses 60 minutes. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/daemon.js |
| Safe plugin discovery | Plugin UI scans ports `3456` through `3460` and connects to `ws://127.0.0.1:<port>/plugin`; daemon default is `3456`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/plugin/ui.html |
| Daemon commands | `figma-cli daemon status [--debug]`, `daemon start [--force]`, `daemon stop`, `daemon restart`, `daemon reconnect`, `daemon diagnose`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/REFERENCE.md |

### Command surface (grouped; tag each READ-ONLY / MUTATING / DESTRUCTIVE)

Tags mean: `READ-ONLY` reads Figma/local state or writes export files without changing the Figma document; `MUTATING` changes the Figma document or local tool config/app/plugin state; `DESTRUCTIVE` deletes Figma document content, variables, collections, or removes installed/local resources.

| Group | Command | Tag | Purpose / key flags |
|---|---|---:|---|
| Setup | `figma-cli` | MUTATING | First-run wizard: checks Node, patches Figma if needed, starts Figma. |
| Setup | `init` / `setup` | MUTATING | Interactive setup; `setup` aliases `init`. |
| Setup | `status` | READ-ONLY | Checks CDP and daemon status. |
| Setup | `connect [--safe]` | MUTATING | Starts Yolo CDP mode or Safe plugin mode. |
| Setup | `unpatch` | MUTATING | Restores Figma `app.asar` patch. |
| Setup | `diagnose` | READ-ONLY | Checks system compatibility and connection status. |
| Daemon | `daemon status [--debug]` | READ-ONLY | Daemon health/token diagnostics. |
| Daemon | `daemon diagnose` | READ-ONLY | Full daemon troubleshooting. |
| Daemon | `daemon start [--force]` | MUTATING | Starts daemon and generates token. |
| Daemon | `daemon stop` | MUTATING | Stops daemon. |
| Daemon | `daemon restart` | MUTATING | Restarts daemon and regenerates token. |
| Daemon | `daemon reconnect` | MUTATING | Reconnects daemon to Figma. |
| Agent setup | `init-agent [--tool claude|cursor|both] [--force]` | MUTATING | Writes `.cursor/rules/figma-cli.mdc` and/or `AGENTS.md` in the current project. |
| Design import/export | `import <source> [-c name] [--save file] [--type tailwind|css|tokens|storybook|designmd] [--print-context]` | MUTATING | Imports DESIGN.md/Tailwind/CSS/tokens/Storybook into variables; Storybook-only import writes component context but no variables. |
| Design import/export | `extract [output] [--sections list] [--pages list] [--selection] [--split] [--no-split]` | READ-ONLY | Exports open Figma file to DESIGN.md / optional structure files. |
| Design import/export | `spec <component> [-f file] [--check nodeId] [--tolerance px]` | READ-ONLY | Reads DESIGN.md spec; `--check` measures built node and exits non-zero on mismatch. |
| Variables | `var list` / `variables list` | READ-ONLY | Lists variables. |
| Variables | `var find <pattern>` | READ-ONLY | Finds variables by pattern. |
| Variables | `var visualize [collection]` | MUTATING | Creates color swatches on canvas. |
| Variables | `var create <name> -c collection -t type [-v value]` | MUTATING | Creates one variable. |
| Variables | `var create-batch <json> -c collection` | MUTATING | Creates multiple variables. |
| Variables | `var bind-batch <json>` | MUTATING | Binds variables to multiple nodes. |
| Variables | `var set-batch <json> [-c collection]` | MUTATING | Batch sets fill/stroke/radius/opacity/name/visible/position/size. |
| Variables | `var rename-batch <json>` | MUTATING | Batch renames nodes. |
| Variables | `var delete-all [-c collection]` | DESTRUCTIVE | Deletes all local variables/collections or one collection’s variables. |
| Variables | `var delete-batch <nodeIds>` | DESTRUCTIVE | Deletes multiple nodes. |
| Collections | `collections list` / `col list` | READ-ONLY | Lists variable collections. |
| Collections | `collections create <name>` / `col create <name>` | MUTATING | Creates a collection. |
| Tokens | `tokens tailwind [-c collection]` | MUTATING | Creates Tailwind color variables. |
| Tokens | `tokens preset <shadcn|radix>` | MUTATING | Adds named token preset. |
| Tokens | `tokens shadcn [-c collection]` | MUTATING | Creates shadcn/ui color primitives. |
| Tokens | `tokens spacing [-c collection]` | MUTATING | Creates spacing scale. |
| Tokens | `tokens radii [-c collection]` | MUTATING | Creates radius scale. |
| Tokens | `tokens import <file> [-c collection] [--force-slash]` | MUTATING | Imports JSON tokens. |
| Tokens | `tokens import-design-md <file> [-c collection] [--print-context]` | MUTATING | Imports DESIGN.md machine-readable tokens. |
| Tokens | `tokens overlap <collections...> [--json]` | READ-ONLY | Compares token names across collections. |
| Tokens | `tokens ds` | MUTATING | Creates IDS base design system. |
| Tokens | `tokens components` | MUTATING | Creates IDS base components. |
| Tokens | `tokens add <name> <value> [-c collection] [-t type]` | MUTATING | Adds one token. |
| Binding | `bind list [-t COLOR|FLOAT]` | READ-ONLY | Lists variables available for binding. |
| Binding | `bind fill|stroke|radius|gap <varName> [-n node]` | MUTATING | Binds selected/specified node property. |
| Binding | `bind padding <varName> [-n node] [-s side]` | MUTATING | Binds padding variable. |
| Creation | `render <jsx> [--parent id] [-x n] [-y n] [--no-smart-position] [--fast] [--as-component] [--keep-wrapper] [-c collection] [--verify]` | MUTATING | Renders JSX to Figma. |
| Creation | `render-batch <jsxArray> [-g gap] [-d row|col] [--as-component] [-c collection] [--verify]` | MUTATING | Renders multiple frames. |
| Creation | `undo` | DESTRUCTIVE | Removes node(s) created by the latest render/render-batch. |
| Creation | `create frame <name> [-w] [-h] [-x] [-y] [--fill] [--radius] [--smart] [-g]` | MUTATING | Creates frame. |
| Creation | `create icon <name> [-s size] [-c color] [-x] [-y] [--spacing]` | MUTATING | Creates Iconify/Lucide-style SVG icon. |
| Creation | `create image <url> [-w] [-h] [-x] [-y] [-n name] [--spacing]` | MUTATING | Creates image node from URL. |
| Creation aliases | `rect|rectangle`, `ellipse|circle`, `text`, `line`, `component`, `group`, `autolayout|al` | MUTATING | Source registers these as top-level legacy/convenience commands; REFERENCE also shows some as `create ...`, but current scanned source only proved top-level aliases. |
| Layout | `sizing hug|fill [-a axis]`, `sizing fixed <w> [h]` | MUTATING | Sets auto-layout sizing. |
| Layout | `padding|pad <value> [r] [b] [l]` | MUTATING | Sets CSS-style padding. |
| Layout | `gap <value>` | MUTATING | Sets auto-layout gap. |
| Layout | `align <start|center|end|stretch>` | MUTATING | Sets alignment. |
| Layout | `set autolayout|al <row|col> [-g] [-p] [--px] [--py] [-n] [-q] [--sizing] [--align] [--wrap] [--fill-children]` | MUTATING | Applies auto-layout. |
| Layout | `set pin <edge> [-n] [-q] [-o] [--offset-x] [--offset-y] [--start] [--end]` | MUTATING | Sets constraints/pinning. |
| Layout | `arrange [-g gap] [-c cols]` | MUTATING | Rearranges all top-level frames; source calls it destructive because it sorts/repositions. |
| Layout | `unstack [-g gap] [--dry-run]` | MUTATING | Spreads overlapping top-level nodes; `--dry-run` is READ-ONLY. |
| Modification | `set fill|stroke|radius|size|scale|pos|opacity|name|text ... [-n] [-q]` | MUTATING | Changes selected/specified/query-matched nodes; stroke has `-w`, scale has `--keep-spacing`. |
| Modification | `use <collection>` / `theme <collection> [-n] [-a] [--dry-run]` | MUTATING | Rebinds variable references to another collection; `--dry-run` is READ-ONLY. |
| Modification | `unwrap <nodeId> [--keep-wrapper]` | DESTRUCTIVE | Moves children out and deletes wrapper unless `--keep-wrapper`. |
| Query/select | `canvas info` | READ-ONLY | Canvas bounds/element count/free space. |
| Query/select | `canvas next [-g gap] [-d right|below]` | READ-ONLY | Computes next free position. |
