Evidence for command surface: `REFERENCE.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, and remote scan of all `src/commands/*.js`. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/REFERENCE.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/CLAUDE.md, https://api.github.com/repos/silships/figma-cli/git/trees/main?recursive=1

### init-agent + generated files

| Item | Finding |
|---|---|
| Command | `figma-cli init-agent [--tool claude|cursor|both] [--force]`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/init.js |
| Cursor file | Writes `.cursor/rules/figma-cli.mdc` with YAML frontmatter and rules. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/init.js |
| Claude/Codex/shared file | Writes `AGENTS.md`; source comment says Claude Code, Cursor, and Codex read it. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/init.js |
| Overwrite behavior | Does not clobber unrelated existing files unless `--force`; if existing file already contains `# Using figma-cli`, returns up-to-date. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/init.js |
| DESIGN.md | Known fact said `init-agent` writes `DESIGN.md`; I could not verify that. Current `src/commands/init.js` only writes Cursor rules and `AGENTS.md`. `DESIGN.md` is produced by `extract` or `import --save` / Storybook import paths, not `init-agent`. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/init.js, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/docs/COMMANDS.md |

### Design-system I/O

| Area | Finding |
|---|---|
| DESIGN.md export | `figma-cli extract [output]` scans the open file and writes a DESIGN.md; default is all pages/all sections, with `--pages`, `--selection`, `--sections`, `--split`, and `--no-split`. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/docs/COMMANDS.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/extract.js |
| DESIGN.md sections | Exporter emits 11 sections: Identity, Structure, Color, Typography, Spacing & Layout, Depth & Motion, Components, States, Rules, Extending this system, Machine-readable tokens. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/design-extract.js |
| Machine-readable block | Importer expects `## 11. Machine-readable tokens` with fenced block ````json design-tokens` containing color, typography, spacing, radius, shadow, fonts, and meta. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/design-md.js |
| Other DESIGN.md formats | Importer also accepts YAML frontmatter specs with top-level `colors`/`color`, `typography`, `rounded`/`radius`/`radii`, `spacing`, `shadow`, and prose color rows like `**Name** (\`#hex\`): role`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/design-md.js |
| Import sources | `figma-cli import <source>` supports DESIGN.md, `tailwind.config.js/.cjs/.ts`, CSS files such as `globals.css`/`styles.css`, W3C/Style Dictionary `tokens.json`, Storybook URL, and `./storybook-static/`. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/docs/COMMANDS.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/setup.js |
| Import options | `-c/--collection`, `--save <file>`, `--type <tailwind|css|tokens|storybook|designmd>`, `--print-context`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/setup.js |
| Storybook behavior | Storybook import yields component names/variants only and does not create Figma variables; docs say combine with Tailwind/CSS import for tokens. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/docs/COMMANDS.md |
| Export targets | Exports PNG/JPG/SVG/PDF screenshots or nodes, CSS variables, Tailwind config, JSX/React, Storybook stories, and DESIGN.md. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/REFERENCE.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/export-eval.js |
| Token binding syntax | `var:name` works in `render`, `create`, and `set`, e.g. `bg="var:card"`, `color="var:foreground"`, `figma-cli set fill "var:primary"`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/CLAUDE.md |
| Collection pinning | `render`/`render-batch` support `--collection <name>`; per-attribute syntax `var:collection:name` can force a specific collection. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/CLAUDE.md |

### Does figma-cli ship/spawn its own MCP? (yes/no + evidence)

No.

Evidence:

| Evidence checked | Result |
|---|---|
| Repo tree | No file/directory named MCP and no obvious MCP server entrypoint. Source: https://api.github.com/repos/silships/figma-cli/git/trees/main?recursive=1 |
| Remote text scan | I scanned README, REFERENCE, CLAUDE, package.json, docs, `src/**`, and `plugin/**` for `mcp` and `model context protocol`; zero hits. |
| Package bin/scripts | Repo `package.json` exposes only `figma-ds-cli` and `figma-cli`, both mapped to `src/index.js`; scripts only include `test`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/package.json |
| Daemon | The bundled daemon is figma-cli’s own HTTP/WebSocket bridge for Figma Desktop, not an MCP server. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/daemon.js |

Conclusion: “install the MCP inside it” cannot mean a figma-cli-owned MCP subcommand/server based on current sources. It likely refers to the separate official Figma MCP server or another external MCP integration, not figma-cli itself.

### Auth / offline

| Topic | Finding |
|---|---|
| Figma auth/API key | No Figma API key required; tool uses Figma Desktop and existing local Figma session/plugin API, not Figma REST. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/README.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md |
| Figma account | npm docs say Figma Desktop with a free account works. Source: https://www.npmjs.com/package/figma-ds-cli |
| Daemon auth | Local daemon uses generated session token header; token file is `~/.figma-ds-cli/.daemon-token`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/daemon.js |
| Cloud/offline | README claims local operation and support for local LLMs via LM Studio/Ollama, fully offline/no cloud/no key. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/README.md |
| Exceptions | Some features necessarily call network or need external auth: `remove-bg` needs a remove.bg API key; Iconify/image/URL/Storybook/website commands may depend on network/local servers. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/REFERENCE.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/url-tools.js |

### Gotchas, risks, platform constraints

| Risk | Detail |
|---|---|
| npm vs repo mismatch | Repo `main` is `1.2.0` and exposes `figma-cli`; npm latest fetch shows `1.0.0` and only `figma-ds-cli`. A skill should not assume `figma-cli` exists after `npm install -g figma-ds-cli` unless installing from repo/current unpublished package or verifying PATH. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/package.json, https://registry.npmjs.org/figma-ds-cli/latest |
| macOS support is the documented baseline | Architecture docs say macOS only; platform source has Windows/Linux helpers, but docs/npm still frame Windows/Linux as not primary/supported. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md, https://www.npmjs.com/package/figma-ds-cli |
| Yolo patch risk | Yolo modifies Figma Desktop `app.asar` and may need Full Disk Access/admin rights; a Figma update may invalidate the patch string. Revert exists via `figma-cli unpatch`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/figma-patch.js |
| Safe mode operational friction | Safe mode requires importing the plugin manifest once and keeping `Plugins → Development → FigCli` open each session. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/REFERENCE.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/plugin/ui.html |
| Daemon/token failures | “Unauthorized: Invalid or missing token” is expected if token/daemon mismatch; docs recommend `figma-cli daemon diagnose` then `figma-cli daemon restart`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/REFERENCE.md |
| Command docs drift | Current docs mention `figma-cli voice`, `figma-cli chat`, and `figma-cli prop combine`; remote source scan did not find top-level `voice`, `chat`, or `prop` registrations. Source for docs: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/CLAUDE.md |
| Primitive command drift | REFERENCE shows `create rect/circle/text/line/group/component/autolayout`; source scan proves `create frame/icon/image` plus top-level `rect|ellipse|text|line|component|group|autolayout`. Skill should prefer verified source commands or test `--help` before emitting these. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/REFERENCE.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/create.js |
| `eval` danger | Agent rules explicitly say never use `eval` to create visual nodes because it bypasses positioning/guards; use `render`/`render-batch`. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/CLAUDE.md |
| Deletion guard | Generated agent rules say never delete existing user nodes; skill gating should treat all delete/clear/unlink/uninstall/undo commands as destructive. Source: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/commands/init.js |
| Large DESIGN.md handling | `extract` auto-splits structure above roughly 50k tokens into `DESIGN-structure/`, which means a skill must handle multi-file export artifacts. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/docs/COMMANDS.md, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/design-extract.js |
| Node version nuance | Node `>=18` is declared, and changelog says CI runs Node 18/20/22, but source contains a warning that `figma-use` can be broken on some Node versions if `enableCompileCache` is missing; skill should prefer the repo’s tested Node range and surface daemon/figma-use failures honestly. Sources: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/package.json, https://raw.githubusercontent.com/silships/figma-cli/main/src/lib/cli-core.js |

### Confidence + unknowns (what you could NOT verify, and why)

Confidence: high for repo `main` behavior, command registrations, patch/daemon model, DESIGN.md format, and “no bundled MCP,” because these were verified from raw source and package metadata.

Unknowns / caveats:

| Unknown | Why |
|---|---|
| Exact current published install behavior for `figma-cli` binary | npm registry latest fetched as `1.0.0` conflicts with repo `main` `1.2.0`; I did not install or execute the package because this was read-only mode. |
| Whether unpublished npm `1.2.0` exists elsewhere | Public registry `latest` showed only `1.0.0`; no write/exec install test performed. |
| Runtime success on Windows/Linux | Source contains platform paths, but docs still say macOS-only/Windows-Linux coming. I did not run platform tests. |
| Voice/chat commands | `CLAUDE.md` references them, but source command registration scan did not show top-level `voice` or `chat`; likely docs are ahead of registered CLI or plugin-based workflow is incomplete in scanned files. |
| Official Figma MCP details | Explicitly out of scope per user instruction; only checked whether figma-cli itself bundles/spawns/references MCP.
